<HEADLINE>
Barbecues, fireworks in Kending National Park could lead to fines
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pingtung  County,  Sept.  21  (CNA) 09/21/07  22:14:01 (By Han
Nai-kuo)
</P>
<P>
The Kending National Park Administration  warned Friday that
people celebrating the Moon Festival next week will not be
allowed to barbecue, set off fireworks or build bonfires in the
park, with violators subject to fines.
</P>
<P>
Administration officials said patrol units will enforce the rules
strictly during the holiday from Sept. 22 until Mid-Autumn
Festival Sept. 25.
</P>
<P>
They added that firework  sellers  could be fined between
NT$300,000 and NT$1.5 million (US$45,380) , while those who set
off fireworks, build bonfires or barbecue in the park could be
fined NT$3,000.
</P>
<P>
The park administration officials said they encourage members of
the public to report offenses by calling 0800-885-996.
</P>
